            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "> The error message number 2 above is the case so it is not misleading.\r\n\r\n@PaulWessel while I understand your argumentation I see a bit of a problem for new users which are encouraged to only learn modern mode. Error message 2 is technically correct but hard to comprehend:\r\n\r\n* `gmt text -L`: Calling a modern mode module with correct options and everything is fine\r\n* `gmt plot -L`: Calling a modern mode module with a single incorrect option and now I'm supposed to know that I'm running in classic mode to make sense of the error message?\r\n\r\nFrom a user perspective it is not clear why running a seemingly modern mode command `gmt plot` with a single incorrect option `-L` beams me into classic mode. Without that knowledge error message 2 doesn't make much sense. \r\n\r\nI know little about how GMT decides what's classic and what's modern mode. From experience I'm sure a lot of thought went into this mechanism. But maybe the case presented here is worth a second look?",
